

### ðŸ§° 1. **Install AWscli

curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install --update
aws --version


---

2. **Configure AWS Credentials (Access Key, Secret)**


aws configure
```

Enter:

* AWS Access Key ID
* AWS Secret Access Key
* Default region (e.g., `ap-south-1`)
* Default output format: `json`

---

 3. **Install `eksctl` (tool to create EKS cluster)**

curl --silent --location "https://github.com/eksctl-io/eksctl/releases/latest/download/eksctl_$(uname -s)_amd64.tar.gz" | tar xz -C /tmp
sudo mv /tmp/eksctl /usr/local/bin
eksctl version



---

4. **Install `kubectl` (to interact with the cluster)**

curl -LO https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.29.3/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
kubectl version --client


Should return: `Client Version: v1.29.3`

---

5. **Create EKS Cluster (Free Tier compatible)**

```bash
eksctl create cluster \
--name demo \
--region ap-south-1 \
--nodegroup-name demo-nodes2 \
--node-type t3.micro \
--nodes 2 \
--nodes-min 1 \
--nodes-max 2 \
--managed
```


---

6. **Verify the Cluster**


kubectl get nodes
```


